# CNPM Fe — Project Profile

A frontend app scaffolded with TanStack Start (file-based router on Vite, React 19) for the CNPM (software engineering project) coursework. The project is at an early stage — most feature code was reset; the live tree currently contains only the router shell, root layout, and a single index route.

## Tech Stack (source of truth: `package.json`)

- **Build**: Vite 8 (config: `vite.config.ts`) with the TanStack Start plugin (`@tanstack/react-start/plugin/vite`), `@tanstack/router-plugin`, `@tailwindcss/vite`, `@tanstack/devtools-vite`
- **Runtime**: React 19, TypeScript 6, ESM (`"type": "module"`)
- **Package manager**: yarn 4 (Berry, `packageManager: yarn@4.15.0`) — `yarn.lock` is the source of truth. `.yarn/releases/yarn-4.15.0.cjs` is checked in.
- **Routing**: `@tanstack/react-router` with **file-based routing** under `src/routes/`. The route tree is generated into `src/routeTree.gen.ts` by the router plugin (do NOT edit the generated file by hand).
- **Server / SSR**: `@tanstack/react-start` (TanStack Start) — supports server functions and SSR. Bootstrap router lives in `src/router.tsx`.
- **State**: client → `@tanstack/store` + `@tanstack/react-store`. Server-state cache library is **not** installed; data fetching is via router loaders / server functions until a query lib is added.
- **Forms**: `@tanstack/react-form` + `zod` v4 for schemas (no `react-hook-form` — do not introduce it).
- **UI / styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 (via `@tailwindcss/vite` and `@import 'tailwindcss'` in `src/styles.css`) + `tw-animate-css`. **shadcn/ui is configured** in `components.json` (`style: "new-york"`, `baseColor: "zinc"`, `iconLibrary: "lucide"`) but no primitives have been generated yet — the `src/components/ui` folder will be created by the first `shadcn add`.
- **Class merger**: `cn()` exported from `src/lib/utils.ts` (uses `clsx` + `tailwind-merge`). Always merge classes through `cn()`.
- **Icons**: `lucide-react`.
- **Tests**: Vitest 4 + `@testing-library/react` + `@testing-library/dom` + `jsdom`. There is no `vitest.config.*` and no setup file checked in — Vitest reads from `vite.config.ts` and uses defaults until those are added.
- **Lint / format**: ESLint 9 (flat config) extending `@tanstack/eslint-config` + Prettier 3 (`prettier.config.js`: `semi: false`, `singleQuote: true`, `trailingComma: 'all'`).
- **Git hooks / CI / commitlint**: not configured in this repo.

## Entry Points

- `src/router.tsx` — `getRouter()` creates the TanStack Router (`scrollRestoration`, `defaultPreload: 'intent'`, `defaultPreloadStaleTime: 0`). Augments the `@tanstack/react-router` `Register` interface so route types are global.
- `src/routes/__root.tsx` — root route. Owns `<head>` (meta, title, stylesheet link to `../styles.css?url`), the HTML shell (`shellComponent: RootDocument`), the `<TanStackDevtools>` panel, and `<Scripts />`.
- `src/routes/index.tsx` — `/` route (file-based via `createFileRoute`).
- `src/routeTree.gen.ts` — **generated** route tree. Do NOT edit. Re-runs on `dev` / `build` via the router plugin.
- `src/styles.css` — Tailwind v4 entry, custom design tokens (`--sea-ink`, `--lagoon`, `--palm`, `--sand`, …), `oklch()` colour scale, dark-mode tokens under `.dark`, and the `@theme inline` block that maps tokens to Tailwind utility classes.
- `src/lib/utils.ts` — `cn()` helper.

## Path Aliases

Both aliases resolve to `./src/*`:

| Alias | Configured in | Use for |
|---|---|---|
| `#/*` | `package.json` `imports`, `tsconfig.json` `paths`, **`components.json` aliases** | Preferred — this is what shadcn writes. New code SHOULD use `#/`. |
| `@/*` | `tsconfig.json` `paths` | Legacy / IDE-friendly. Acceptable in handwritten code; do not mix in the same file. |

Always use one of the aliases. Never use deep relative paths (`../../..`).

## Scripts (ONLY scripts from `package.json` — never invent commands)

```
yarn dev       # vite dev --port 5173
yarn build     # vite build
yarn preview   # vite preview
yarn test      # vitest run
yarn lint      # eslint
yarn format    # prettier --write . && eslint --fix
yarn check     # prettier --check .
```

There is **no** `type-check` script. For TypeScript verification, run `yarn tsc --noEmit` (the compiler is a project devDependency).

Do NOT run `dev` / `build` proactively — assume the user is already running them. Use `yarn lint`, `yarn check`, and `yarn tsc --noEmit` to verify changes.

## Adding shadcn primitives

`components.json` is configured. Add primitives with the latest shadcn CLI (yarn equivalent of the workspace `.cursorrules` pnpm command):

```bash
yarn dlx shadcn@latest add button
```

Generated primitives land in `src/components/ui/`. Aliases resolved by shadcn: `components → #/components`, `ui → #/components/ui`, `utils → #/lib/utils`, `lib → #/lib`, `hooks → #/hooks`. The `cn` import shadcn writes is `import { cn } from '#/lib/utils'`.

## Where to Look First

| If you need to… | Go to |
|---|---|
| Add a route | Create a new `src/routes/<path>.tsx` (file-based) — the router plugin regenerates `routeTree.gen.ts` |
| Edit the HTML shell / global `<head>` | `src/routes/__root.tsx` |
| Edit global tokens / Tailwind theme | `src/styles.css` (`:root`, `.dark`, `@theme inline`) |
| Add a UI primitive | `yarn dlx shadcn@latest add <name>` → lands in `src/components/ui/` |
| Add a shared composite component | `src/components/<name>.tsx` (folder created when first added) |
| Touch the class-merge helper | `src/lib/utils.ts` |
| Configure router options | `src/router.tsx` |

## Local Workspace Hygiene

- `.cursor/` STAYS tracked in git — it ships project intelligence and must be reviewed.
- `.gitignore` already excludes `node_modules`, `dist`, `.tanstack`, `.nitro`, `.vinxi`, `.output`, `.wrangler`, `.env`, `*.local`.
- `.env` is git-ignored — environment keys are project-local. Do NOT commit it.

## Do NOT

- Introduce a new framework, router, validator, ORM, state library, form library, or component kit when an equivalent is already installed (TanStack Router/Start/Store/Form, Zod, Tailwind v4, shadcn, lucide-react are the picks).
- Hand-edit `src/routeTree.gen.ts` — it is regenerated by `@tanstack/router-plugin`.
- Hardcode tokens (hex colours, spacing scales) when a CSS variable already exists in `src/styles.css`.
- Bypass `cn()` by string-concatenating class names.
- Mix `#/` and `@/` aliases in the same import block — pick the one in use elsewhere in the file.
- Call `process.env` directly in client code — read Vite env via `import.meta.env`.
